      <div class="step screensteps-section screensteps-depth-1" id="search_courses" data-step-uuid="ca17e824-1f40-4d4d-9b8f-411234e55990">
    <h2 id="search_courses" class="step-title screensteps-heading">Search Courses</h2>
        <div class="image screensteps-image">
      <a href="https://media.screensteps.com/image_assets/assets/000/750/080/original/83787ac9-0cec-4188-b4a5-ae626bfdfc14.png" class="screensteps-image-zoom" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer">
        <img src="https://media.screensteps.com/image_assets/assets/000/750/080/medium/83787ac9-0cec-4188-b4a5-ae626bfdfc14.png" srcset="" alt="Search Courses" height="551" width="855">
      </a>
  </div>
 
      <div class="step-instructions screensteps-textblock">
  <div id="text-content_6B400E90-1CB8-0135-2F97-22000B5A851D" class="text-block-content">
    <p>You can search for courses in several different ways. In the Name field [1], you can type the name of a course. </p>
<p>You can also search for courses by status. If you want to view only public courses, click the <strong>Public courses only </strong>checkbox [2]. If you want to view only open enrollment courses, click the <strong>Open enrollment courses only </strong>checkbox [3]. Open enrollment courses are courses that you can join at any time.</p>
<p>When you are finished selecting your search options, click the <strong>Search </strong>button [4].</p>
  </div>
</div>
 
  </div>

